# Plataforma IA - Cursor Rules

Read and follow CLAUDE.md before making any implementation decision.

Mandatory rules:
- Follow CLAUDE.md as the source of truth.
- Do not invent modules, screens, flows, business rules, libraries, or infrastructure.
- If something is not defined, ask Davis before implementing.
- Use Node.js 24, TypeScript, pnpm workspaces, NestJS, Prisma, PostgreSQL, Redis, BullMQ, Bull Board, Next.js 14, TailwindCSS, Docker and Docker Compose.
- Never use npm.
- Never use yarn.
- Never use Python.
- Never push.
- Never commit unless Davis explicitly asks.
- Never create frontend screens before backend endpoints.
- Never create dashboard before the first real end-to-end flow.
- Never let AI access external systems directly.
- Never let AI execute business logic directly.
- Never rewrite ERP, payroll, or tax engines.
- Never create a domain table without company_id.
- Never put a specific external system name inside core code.
- All external calls must go through BullMQ queues.
- Payroll integrations are always read only.
- Start with Phase 0 Foundation.
- Test before saying a block is ready.

Workflow with Davis:
- Explain what will be done in one short line before changing files.
- After creating or editing a file, show it with cat and open it in Cursor.
- Use: cat path/to/file && cursor path/to/file
- Wait for Davis approval/output before moving to the next step.
- Use accelerated blocks only when Davis explicitly asks, but still validate results.